{
  "texts": [
    "This was a large, multinational company, and it may be the case that ChatGPT's training data included information about multiple of its locations (but, not likely about this case).",
    "Our finding that complaints written for the SDNY were of a higher standard than those in the District of New Jersey, is intuitive, since more civil securities and commodity suits tend to be filed in the SDNY than any other jurisdiction, so the training data set likely would have included more cases from this jurisdiction, if it included any at all.",
    "For example, in March 2021, 36.8% of suits of this nature were filed in the SDNY, compared to only 11.9% for the next most popular filing jurisdiction (TRAC 2021).",
    "Overall, our results are consistent with prior research that qualitatively determined that ChatGPT showed some skill in drafting legal documents (Iu and Wong 2023; Perlman 2022).",
    "Similarly, Choi et al. (2023) 's finding that ChatGPT performed better on essay questions than multiple choice ones is consistent with our finding that ChatGPT performed better in drafting than in statutory reasoning."
  ]
}